## Purpose

Define the mandatory structure and registration process for component library documentation pages. Every component — LD primitive or WCP product-level — MUST have a page (or be added to an existing grouped page) in the Component Library.

---

## Page Structure Requirements

Every component library page MUST include:

### 1. ComponentPageLayout Wrapper

```tsx
import { ComponentPageLayout } from '@/components/ui/ComponentPageLayout';

export default function MyComponentPage() {
  return (
    <ComponentPageLayout
      section="WCP Components"  // or "LD Components", "Patterns"
      title="My Component"
      description="One-line description of the component and its use cases."
    >
      {/* page content */}
    </ComponentPageLayout>
  );
}
```

Note: Pages use `export default` (unlike components which use named exports).

### 2. Interactive Demo

A live, stateful demo where users can interact with the component. Use `useState` to make props controllable.

### 3. All Variants and States

Show every variant, size, and state the component supports. Each should be in a labeled card with a brief note.

### 4. Usage Notes

A bullet list covering:
- Available props and their values
- Accepted content types or constraints
- Responsive behavior
- Accessibility considerations

---

## Grouping Policy — When to Share a Page

Similar components MUST be grouped on a single page rather than getting separate pages:

| Component type | Group on page |
|---------------|---------------|
| Item tile variants (WCPItemTile, FlashDealsItemTile, PromotionalItemTile) | **Item Tile** |
| Carousel components (FlashDealsCarousel, NewArrivalsCarousel, JumpRightBackIn) | **Carousels & Product Grids** |
| Order/status cards (ActiveCurbsideCard, OrderStatusCard, OrderStatusBanner) | **Order & Status Cards** |
| Banner variants (BasicBanner, SkylineBanner, PromoBanner) | **Promo Banners** |
| Dropdown components (AccountDropdown, ReorderDropdown, DepartmentsDropdown) | **Dropdowns** |

Only create a new standalone page when the component represents a genuinely new pattern with no existing group.

---

## Registration Checklist (ALL Required)

After creating the page file, you MUST complete all of these steps:

### Step 1 — Lazy import in App.tsx

```tsx
const MyComponentPage = React.lazy(() => import('./pages/component-library/MyComponent'));
```

### Step 2 — Route in App.tsx

```tsx
<Route path="my-component" element={<MyComponentPage />} />
```

### Step 3 — Sidebar entry in ComponentLibraryLayout.tsx

Add to the correct section in `navigationSections`:

```ts
{ id: 'my-component', nameKey: 'componentLibrary.navMyComponent', path: '/component-library/my-component' },
```

| Component type | Sidebar section |
|---------------|----------------|
| WCP product components | `componentLibrary.wcpComponents` |
| WCP page/layout patterns | `componentLibrary.wcpPatterns` |
| LD 3.5 primitives | `componentLibrary.components` |
| Shared/Radix components | `componentLibrary.sharedSection` |

**Without this step, the page is unreachable from the sidebar.**

### Step 4 — Overview.tsx card entry

```ts
{
  titleKey: 'componentLibrary.navMyComponent',
  descKey: 'componentLibrary.descMyComponent',
  path: '/component-library/my-component',
  icon: 'Note',
  section: 'wcp'  // or 'ld'
},
```

### Step 5 — i18n keys in ALL THREE locale files

Add to `client/locales/en/common.json`, `es/common.json`, and `fr/common.json`:

```json
"navMyComponent": "My Component",
"descMyComponent": "Short description for the Overview card"
```

