## Page CSS Module Pattern

Use a dedicated CSS module for the page. Common classes:

```css
.page { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 32px; }
.section { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }
.sectionTitle {
  font-family: var(--ld-semantic-font-family-sans);
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--ld-semantic-color-text);
  margin: 0;
}
.grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  gap: 16px;
}
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
```

---

## Common Mistakes

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Missing sidebar entry | Page exists but unreachable — always add to `ComponentLibraryLayout.tsx` |
| Missing i18n keys | Sidebar shows raw key string — add to all 3 locale files |
| No interactive demo | Page is static documentation only — add `useState` controls |
| Hardcoded styles in page | Use CSS modules with semantic tokens, same as components |
| Duplicate page for variant | Add to existing grouped page instead |

---

## Enforcement Level

**HIGH** — Every component must be documented. A component without a library page is considered incomplete.
